http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/Vijayawada/Congress-flays-TDP-on-drought/article13988102.ece

Blaming the TDP government for obtaining inadequate financial assistance from the Centre to tackle drought in the State, the Andhra Pradesh Congress Committee (APCC) has demanded that the government convene an all-party meet to prepare an action plan to help farmers.The Centre on Wednesday had announced a financial assistance of Rs 433.77 crore to AP to tackle drought, while Rs.815 crore was sanctioned to Odisha and Rs. 1304.52 crore to Uttar Pradesh. The State government had declared 359 mandals as drought-hit and sought a financial aid of Rs.2,059 crore.